name: 1970 Targa Florio “Ace of Diamond N°12” Porsche 908/3 | 1/5
description:
The 908/3 is a special car. Radical lightweight construction but produce almost perfect weight distribution.

The air-cooled 2,997 cc twin-valve 8 cylinder flat engine, type 908 initially delivered 370 HP.

Designed by Porsche especially for use on just two tracks in the Targa Florio and Nürburgring Nordschleife in 1970 and 1971.
